main event: A UFO sighting involving a round object the size of a dime, drifting northwest in Wheaton, Illinois on May 20, 1956.
interesting points: The object had a distinct reddish-purple color,The sighting lasted for approximately 25 minutes,The sighting was classified as a ground-visual observation,Comments suggest the object could be the planet Venus or a balloon,The report is part of Project Blue Book documentation.
sighted object: one round object the size of a dime
